com.camerontec.catalys.util.data

Class AbstractTagValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.AbstractTagValuesReadable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.AbstractTagValues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, IFIXBytesImportable, ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValueIteratorBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValues, ITagValuesReadable, FIXBytesImportable, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<ITagValue>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OrderedTagValues, TagValuesAsArray, TagValuesAsIndexedByteArray, TagValuesAsIndexedList, TagValuesAsList

    public abstract class AbstractTagValues
extends AbstractTagValuesReadable
implements ITagValues, FIXBytesImportable
    This class provides a skeletal implementation of the ITagValues interface to minimize the effort required to implement this interface backed by a collection of ITagValue objects.

    To use this as a base for your own ITagValues implementation you need to provide implementations for the methods mentioned in the AbstractTagValuesReadable JavaDoc as well as for the following methods:

    • addFieldBase(ITagValue)
    • clone() - the existing implementation which just calls Object.clone() is unlikely to be suitable.
    • removeFieldBase(int)
    • updateFieldValue(int,IValue)
    Optionally, you may also want to override the following methods in order to provide a more efficient implementation than the default.
    • clearTagValues()
    • copyFrom(ITagValues)

    You may also want to override getFreeTagValue() if you are supporting reuse.

    If you want to intercept all modifying methods, override the following with your own versions which do whatever extra processing you wish, then call the super method to actually perform the update. All modifying methods ultimately go through one of these methods.

    • addField(ITagValue)
    • removeField(int)
    • setFieldValue(int, IValue)

    As an example of an ITagValues implementation based on this class, see TagValuesAsArray.

    To test an ITagValues implementation, you should subclass ITagValuesTestCaseBase. For example, see the test case for TagValuesAsIndexedList in TagValuesAsIndexedListTestCase.

      • addField

        public final void addField(ITagValue field)
        Description copied from interface: ITagValues
        Add the given field to the end of the list of fields.

        Note that ITagValue objects may be reused across multiple method invocations by ITagValues implementations. If you retrieved the 'field' object from a different ITagValues you should make a copy and pass the copy into this method.

        Alternatively, you can use ITagValues.addField(int, IValue) which does exactly that, e.g. addField(field.getTag(), field.getValue()).

        Specified by:
        addField in interface ITagValues
        Parameters:
        field - Field to be added.

        public final void clearTagValues()
        Description copied from interface: ITagValues
        Clears out any existing message content - leaving an empty message, ie a message with no fields.

        Specified by:

      • clearTagValuesBase

        protected void clearTagValuesBase()
        The default implementation just calls AbstractTagValuesReadable.getTagValues() and calls removeField(int) for the tag associated with each element in the returned array.

        It is likely that you may want to override this with a more efficient method that has knowledge about the details of the class's implementation.

      • copyImplementationDetailsFrom

        protected void copyImplementationDetailsFrom(ITagValues other)
        Empty implementation here. Can be overwritten by subclasses to copy implementation specific details in addition to the message fields.

        This method is called by copyFrom(ITagValues) if this.getClass().isAssignableFrom(other.getClass()).

        If you overwrite this method you probably should overwrite AbstractTagValuesReadable.isEqualImplementation(ITagValuesReadable) as well.

        Parameters:
        other - ITagValues to copy from.

      • appendFieldsFrom

        protected void appendFieldsFrom(ITagValues other)
        The default implementation just calls AbstractTagValuesReadable.iterator() on the given other ITagValues, copies each element and adds the copy using addField(ITagValue). Undefined fields are not copied/appended.

        It is likely that you may want to override this with a more efficient method that has knowledge about the details of the AbstractTagValues subclass' implementations.

        Parameters:
        other - ITagValues to copy from.
        See Also:
        IValue.isUndefined()

      • removeAllFields

        public void removeAllFields(BitSet tagsToRemove)
        Description copied from interface: ITagValues
        Removes all instances of the specified fields.

        This method is a more efficient alternative to ITagValues.removeAllFields(int), which must be called repeatedly for each tag.

        Specified by:
        removeAllFields in interface ITagValues
        Parameters:
        tagsToRemove - A BitSet that defines the tags to remove. The bit index corresponds to a specific tag number; setting a bit to true indicates that the tag should be removed if present in the message. It is recommended that the caller does not create a new set for each call, in order to eliminate garbage creation.

      • setFieldValue

        public final void setFieldValue(int tag,
                                IValue value)
        Description copied from interface: ITagValues
        Sets the value of the first tag/value field with the given tag.

        If no such entry exists it is created.

        If the entry already exists, its value is updated.

        If value is null, the entry is removed if present.

        Note that IValue objects may be reused across multiple method invocations so the internal implementation should NOT store a reference to the IValue object passed in. It should copy its contents.

        Specified by:
        setFieldValue in interface ITagValues
        Parameters:
        tag - Tag number.
        value - New value for entry.

      • updateFieldValue

        public final void setValue(int tag,
                           byte[] value)
        Description copied from interface: ITagValues
        Sets the value of the first tag/value field with the given tag.

        If no such entry exists it is created.

        If the entry already exists, its value is updated.

        If value is null, the entry is removed if present.

        Note that only a reference to the byte array is stored - a copy is NOT made. If this is not what you want, you should make the copy yourself and pass the copy into this method.

      • importBytes

        public final void importBytes(String dictionaryName,
                              BytesSegment bytesToImport,
                              boolean dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXBytesImportable
        Import the specified FIX bytes.
        Specified by:
        importBytes in interface IFIXBytesImportable
        Parameters:
        dictionaryName - A name of FIX dictionary used for getting a FIX field type, couldn't be null
        bytesToImport - BytesSegment representing FIX bytes (SOH separated tag values, ending with SOH)
        dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData - True to indicate that no special treatment is to be given to raw data and their associated length fields (that is, they are expected to conform to regular FIX field content and in particular the data field should not contain FIX SOH), false to treat the data field as opaque and use its preceding length field (if any) to determine its length.

      • importBytes

        public final void importBytes(String dictionaryName,
                              BytesSegment bytesToImport,
                              boolean dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData,
                              boolean useExactFixDictionary)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXBytesImportable
        Import the specified FIX bytes.
        Specified by:
        importBytes in interface IFIXBytesImportable
        Parameters:
        dictionaryName - A name of FIX dictionary used for getting a FIX field type. May be null, if and only if IFIXMessageSpecifics.getUseExactFixDictionary() returns false.
        bytesToImport - BytesSegment representing FIX bytes (SOH separated tag values, ending with SOH)
        dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData - True to indicate that no special treatment is to be given to raw data and their associated length fields (that is, they are expected to conform to regular FIX field content and in particular the data field should not contain FIX SOH), false to treat the data field as opaque and use its preceding length field (if any) to determine its length.
        useExactFixDictionary - If true dictionaryName supplied will be used for getting a FIX field type otherwise FIXVersion.FIX_LATEST.
